Share

      house. They are all grown up now, it's difficult for them to 
share a room.
IMAN
It will take several months.
NAJMEH
It doesn’t matter.
Iman takes the gun out of the drawer and shows it to Najmeh. 
Najmeh is taken aback and looks at it with fear.
IMAN
Don't be afraid, they gave it to me for personal protection.
Najmeh contemplates for a moment.
IMAN
try it...
NAJMEH
No, I don't like to, it's dangerous.
IMAN
Take it.
Najmeh holds the gun for a moment. Iman laughs. It's as if he's 
enjoying himself unconsciously. Najmeh returns the gun. Iman 
puts it back in the drawer.
NAJMEH
I think it's time to talk about your job with the girls.
IMAN
Not yet...
NAMJMEH
Why? It's a very good opportunity. You're a judge now! If the 
kids know, they will be proud of you.
IMAN
    

