      Not a judge, an investigating judge.
NAJMEH
Whatever. Soon you'll become an advisory judge and then a chief 
judge, right? Won't you?
Iman nods in approval.
NAJMEH
Well, then the girls need to know these things. It affects their 
behavior. They're young, they must be more considerate because 
of your job.
IMAN
You know the situation is different for revolutionary courts, 
people don't have a positive perception.
NAJMEH
Yes, but we cannot hide it from the kids forever. You always 
waited for an opportunity to talk to them about your job. Now is 
your chance.
Iman takes a moment to think it over.
NAJMEH
Tonight, four of us will go to a restaurant. We'll have a little 
celebration for your promotion, and then we'll have a 
conversation as well and share some things with the kids.
IMAN
How much can we share?
NAJMEH
Leave it to me.
Iman seems to be content with this plan and continues drinking
his tea.
    

